title: Everest Sydney and Caulfield Cup, Melbourne: Punters arrive in colourful frocks
description: Thousands have started streaming into Sydney's Royal Randwick and Melbourne's Caulfield racecourse to secure the best spots to watch two of Australia's biggest horse races.

title: Indiana mom sentenced to 115 YEARS in prison after poisoning ex-boyfriend's oatmeal with fentany
description: An Indiana woman has been sentenced to 115 years in prison after she was found guilty of poisoning her ex-boyfriend's oatmeal and strangling him to death during a custody battle.

title: Aerobic's Oz's Kelly Martinovich's son Jaden Martinovich bashed in prison after alleged stabbing
description: A former TV star's son, alleged to have stabbed a boy to death and boasted about it in a Perth carpark, has been hospitalised after a brutal prison bashing in a Western Australian lockup.

title: Athony Albanese confirms paid parental leave will be extended to six months before Budget
description: Anthony Albanese has confirmed his government will increase the length of paid parental leave to 26 weeks, a move he says is good for the economy and families.

title: Probe launched - Stacey Abrams' group funnels thousands to director's family and friends
description: Stacey Abrams' voting accessibility PAC Fair Fight appears to be paying many thousands of dollars to family and friends of the director who lack political experience or expertise.

title: Hillsong pastor Brian Houston is back in Australia and prepares to fight charges over paedophile dad
description: Brian Houston returned to Australia for a court hearing slated for December where he will defend accusations he failed to report his paedophile dad, Frank Houston, to authorities.

title: Did Eric Adams fail to declare cook book income?
description: Eric Adams in his 2021 Conflict of Interest disclosure said he had received up to $50,000 in an advance for his cookbook, but did not declare any revenue from the book in his tax return.

title: China bombards US warships with drones: One LANDED on deck of destroyer near Hong Kong
description: Navy documents show US fleets were plagued by unidentified drones that appeared to be documenting America's forces in the Pacific since 2017. In all, there were 151 reports made.

title: MRI blunders: Hundreds of patients with metallic implants narrowly avoid death or serious injury
description: Doctors should check medical records before requesting a scan. Hospitals in England recorded 315 near-misses from April 2020 to March 2022 involving patients sent for an MRI.

title: New head of Cambridge University suggests he will ditch plan to decolonise the institution
description: Interim head of Cambridge University Dr Anthony Freeling has suggested he will not continue plans to 'decolonise' the curriculum and claimed to not know what the word meant.

title: HALF of British 16-24-year-olds identify as naturist or nudist: Poll reveals surge in stripping off
description: The biggest survey on nudism to ever take place in the UK, completed by Ipsos Mori, estimated that 6.75 million people engage in naturist activities such as sunbathing and swimming naked.

title: New law would force 40% of trains to run during rail strikes
description: The new laws, which could be brought before Parliament next week, will bring Britain into line with several European countries which have similar measures.

title: Return of the pressure cooker: Sales of energy-saving gadgets that our grandparents used are rising
description: John Lewis says purchases of pressure cookers are up by 110 per cent and slow cookers by 262 per cent. Sales of modern air fryers are also up by 176 per cent.

title: Victoria, Tasmania, Australia weather: More residents evacuated, flood waters expected to peak
description: Police confirmed a man was found dead in floodwaters in the backyard of a Rochester home on Saturday after rivers across northern Victoria burst their banks. More rain is on its way too.

title: British farmers face frightening pumpkin harvest in drought
description: The summer heatwave and drought have reduced pumpkin crops from around 15 million to as few as ten million, experts say.

title: ANDREW NEIL says the radical tax-cutting agenda is dead in the water after another U-turn by the PM
description: ANDREW NEIL: Liz Truss yesterday attempted to restore her Government's credibility with the financial markets by sacking her hapless Chancellor Kwasi Kwarteng.

title: Buckingham Palace hopes to quietly drop Consort from Queen Camilla's title before King's coronation
description: The decision will ultimately be dependent on how warmly the public accepts Camilla as she steps into her new role over the coming months.

title: Star of Netflix's The Crown takes plunge as series recreates Princess Diana's last holiday
description: Perched on the end of a diving board alone with her thoughts, it is one of the last photos taken of Princess Diana before her death.

title: Growing fears that Gordon Brown's pensions timebomb may finally be about to explode
description: The journey to this point began in the late 1990s, when New Labour came to power and Gordon Brown gained control of the nation's purse strings.

title: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: The day may come for the grown-ups in the Tory party to take charge...
description: The day after Tory MPs ousted Boris Johnson from Downing Street, this newspaper asked on its front page: 'What the hell have they done?' Never has this question seemed more prescient.

title: Tory big beast Jeremy Hunt is parachuted in as new Chancellor amid mini-Budget shambles
description: Liz Truss telephoned Jeremy Hunt at 9.30am yesterday after concluding that Kwasi Kwarteng could not credibly continue in office.

title: King Charles III won't move into Buckingham Palace for FIVE YEARS due to £370m renovation
description: As the palace continues its 10-year refurbishment programme, the new King and Queen Consort Camilla are expected to split their time between up to four other castles.

title: Democratic Senate hopeful John Fetterman leads with stroke jokes at Pennsylvania rally
description: John Fetterman led with stroke jokes at a Friday night Pennsylvania rally, as his fitness for office was questioned this week after an interview showed him using closed captioning.
